Advansa Sasa, Deva, Koc Holding: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-04-21T06:13:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/advansa-sasa-deva-koc-holding-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  rose 311.97, or
0.5 percent, to 68,054.04 yesterday.  Advansa Sasa Polyester Sanayi AS (SASA)  : The Turkish
producer of polyester fibers, yarns and plastic bottles, will
pay 21.9 million liras ($14 million) in back-taxes and fines for
2007 and 2010 over three years, reducing the amount from 108.4
million liras after applying to the government’s restructuring
offer, it said in a statement to the Istanbul Stock Exchange
after the market closed yesterday. Advansa Sasa gained 3 kurus,
or 1.4 percent, to 2.15 liras.  Deva Holding AS (DEVA)  : The Turkish drugmaker owned by
EastPharma Ltd. will apply to restructure back-taxes and fines
from 2001-2008 as part of the government offer, according to a
statement to the bourse after the market closed yesterday. Deva
climbed 3 kurus, or 1 percent, to 3.08 liras.  Koc Holding AS (KCHOL)  : Turkey’s biggest group of
companies was cut to “sell” from “neutral” at UBS AG,
according to a report today. Koc Holding fell 8 kurus, or 1
percent, to 7.78 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
